    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <head>No. 197.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L.
                                    West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1886</date>.
                                [Received July 6.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 29th of
                            May, I have the honor to inform you that I am instructed by the Earl of
                            Rosebery to state that the matters therein referred to will receive the
                            careful attention of Her Majesty’s Government after the necessary
                            communication with the Dominion Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
